# Committed build artifacts (minified demo bundles), not source: they carry
# thousands of phantom ast-grep criticals (loose-equality, "secret comparison"
# hits on THREE.js shader code) and stall single-language ubs scans.
website/public/demo/assets/
website/public/demo-preview/assets/
# All integration-test files are assertion-heavy by design; test-assert noise
# belongs in --exclude-tests (critical gate), not the warning-count baseline
# which tracks production-code quality. Blanket tests/ exemption for
# hivemind-ubs-warning-paydown-3164-lkfp (extends the per-file exemptions from
# hivemind-yfbq / hivemind-6dc2.5 to cover all integration tests uniformly).
tests/
# Fidelity/benchmark tooling (benchmarks/fidelity/main.rs et al.) is eval/bench
# code, not production runtime — same rationale as the tests/ exemption above.
# Exemption alex-approved for hivemind-21zi (mirrors the tests/ sign-off in
# hivemind-yfbq). Keeps the warning baseline focused on production-code quality.
benchmarks/
